        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "usp_SBMR_getUnassignedAccountsList",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve a list of unassigned accounts from a billing system. It focuses on accounts that are either associated with a specific facility or agency and are currently active. The procedure joins several tables to gather detailed information about each account, including utility company details, billing group descriptions, and service addresses. It also attempts to match accounts with records in the SBMR (Sales and Billing Management Reporting) system to identify unassigned accounts."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The complexity of this stored procedure is medium due to the following factors:"
